03:05.979 --> 03:10.143
Boys. Time to get up. Come on.

03:11.610 --> 03:14.066
It's Saturday. We've got to get going.

03:14.280 --> 03:17.732
- Where are we going?
- We're going to see my uncle Joe.

03:17.950 --> 03:20.406
What? I don't want to go to Uncle Joe's!

03:20.619 --> 03:23.620
- Come here!
- I don't wanna go!

03:23.831 --> 03:26.952
No, I want to watch my cartoons!
It's Saturday!

03:27.168 --> 03:29.493
You can't make us! We don't wanna go!

03:29.713 --> 03:32.832
- Stop it!
- No, we don't wanna go!

03:33.048 --> 03:38.921
We'll be good! We'll eat anything.
We'll clean our room. But no Uncle Joe.

03:39.139 --> 03:41.012
We don't have time for this.

03:41.224 --> 03:44.178
- Leave us alone!
- You wouldn't hurt Daddy.

03:48.481 --> 03:51.186
- It's early, Carl.
- I want to get there first.

03:51.401 --> 03:56.823
Whoever gets there first talks about you
until there's no point you even being there.

03:57.032 --> 03:59.403
Try to bring up Tina's drinking.

03:59.617 --> 04:02.287
- She's your cousin.
- You're more subtle.

04:11.505 --> 04:12.915
[buzzer]

04:13.131 --> 04:15.420
Carl and Nora McTeague.

04:21.515 --> 04:23.638
Welcome to hell.

04:50.920 --> 04:52.995
- Are we first, Douglas?
- Indeed, sir.

04:53.213 --> 04:57.046
No one else had the presence of mind
to be three hours early.

04:58.719 --> 05:03.215
- May I take your bird, madam?
- No, we'll give it to him ourselves.

05:03.433 --> 05:05.757
Care to wait in the drawing-room?

05:05.976 --> 05:10.685
- There was another car out front. Who...?
- Dr Hemmel is with your uncle.

05:10.898 --> 05:12.357
Anything wrong?

05:12.566 --> 05:16.611
Your uncle was coughing
most of the night, sir.

05:16.821 --> 05:19.692
What kind of cough? Was it dry or liquidy?

05:19.907 --> 05:24.368
It was just a cough, sir.
Next time I'll save you a sample.

05:26.372 --> 05:28.412
[plopping sound]

05:35.506 --> 05:37.416
He'll really like the bird.

05:37.634 --> 05:42.177
- It cost us $400, Carl.
- You have to spend money to make money.

05:42.389 --> 05:45.840
- Oh, my heavens!
- Yolanda, what's wrong?

05:46.058 --> 05:47.434
He's dead!

05:49.103 --> 05:54.181
One minute the doctor was examining him
and he say he was fine, and then...

05:55.694 --> 05:57.485
- He's dead.
- Come quickly!

05:57.696 --> 05:59.320
Yes!

05:59.531 --> 06:01.737
- [boy] Are we rich?
- [Carl] Maybe.

06:08.540 --> 06:10.782
Oh, my God.

06:11.001 --> 06:13.670
[Yolanda wails]

06:13.878 --> 06:16.452
Yolanda, go clean something.

06:21.178 --> 06:23.052
Stop that!

06:29.395 --> 06:31.102
It's Dr Hemmel!

06:31.313 --> 06:33.769
Of course it's Dr Hemmel.

06:33.982 --> 06:38.940
He used to brag how he got up at 5am
to play racket-ball at 71 years old.

06:39.154 --> 06:41.527
You don't hear him bragging now.

06:41.740 --> 06:43.649
[Uncle Joe chuckles]

06:43.867 --> 06:46.441
Truth be known, we are so relieved.

06:46.662 --> 06:49.414
When Yolanda came in screaming,
we thought...

06:49.624 --> 06:54.202
Well, all I can say is we're glad
you're still with us, Uncle Joe.

06:54.419 --> 06:59.462
- You look thrilled.
- We are. Especially the boys. Joe and Joe.

06:59.675 --> 07:04.302
Look, another little Joe in the oven.
Here's a doctor's note to prove it.

07:04.514 --> 07:07.763
- You look nice, Nora.
- Thanks, Uncle Joe. So do you.

07:07.975 --> 07:11.641
- Why don't we just cut the cable?
- It's too thick. Come on.

07:11.854 --> 07:14.559
Did you hear that? He said you look nice.

07:14.774 --> 07:18.724
- I think that's a good sign.
- I don't know what to think.

07:18.945 --> 07:21.649
Carl, I want a girl, honey.

07:21.864 --> 07:26.194
All right. I swear, after he's dead
we'll have a girl, I promise. OK?

07:34.293 --> 07:38.042
Uncle Joe?
Wanted to tell you about something.

07:38.256 --> 07:40.829
You should see how Big Joe...our Big Joe,

07:41.050 --> 07:44.088
what a head for business he has
at nine years old.

07:44.304 --> 07:47.470
He organised a lawn-mowing company
with fourth-graders.

07:47.682 --> 07:52.226
He's preparing himself in case he has to
take over a big business some day.

07:52.437 --> 07:54.476
So you're interested in money, huh?

07:54.689 --> 07:57.263
Uh-huh. Made ten bucks just coming here.

07:58.735 --> 08:01.023
I get another 20 if I kiss you.

08:02.405 --> 08:04.943
I'm thinking about it.

08:08.662 --> 08:10.702
All right.

08:12.583 --> 08:13.958
That's it.

08:24.762 --> 08:28.260
- What happened? Is he...?
- Coronary. He died instantly.

08:28.473 --> 08:32.258
- Really? You mean just...?
- And he left everything to you, sis.

08:32.477 --> 08:35.182
- Really?
- It wasn't him. It was Dr Hemmel.

08:35.397 --> 08:36.808
You son of a bitch.

08:37.025 --> 08:41.650
- You wish it was the old man, don't you?
- I did. Now I wish it was you.

08:41.861 --> 08:46.191
- How are your girls, Ed?
- Yes, we have girls. You know why?

08:46.409 --> 08:52.613
We wouldn't put Ed's sperm in a centrifuge
to separate the X's from the Y's!

08:52.831 --> 08:55.867
Brother, no matter how much
Uncle Joe is worth,

08:56.085 --> 08:59.371
there is a line below which we will not go.

08:59.588 --> 09:02.673
Jolene, Joette? Let's go in, girls.

09:06.720 --> 09:09.342
- We saw an ambulance!
- Dr Hemmel died.

09:09.557 --> 09:11.680
Ah.

09:12.852 --> 09:17.182
[makes flatulence sounds]

09:30.245 --> 09:33.909
Dennis, why don't you go and sit
at the kids' table?

09:34.124 --> 09:35.666
Make me.

09:45.010 --> 09:48.876
- Are you retarded?
- Not according to the tests.

09:49.097 --> 09:51.386
You just sit here and shut up.

09:51.599 --> 09:52.928
[starts again]

09:54.978 --> 09:57.185
- Yolanda!
- It's all over the place!

09:57.398 --> 10:01.062
He has a cold, Uncle Joe.
He didn't want you to get sick.

10:01.276 --> 10:03.601
Ed, your girls knocked over some milk.

10:03.820 --> 10:07.652
Well, Uncle Joe, I guess
you'll have to find a new doctor.

10:07.866 --> 10:12.612
What for? Doctors, medicine.
Who needs 'em, huh?

10:12.830 --> 10:16.199
You know who you should talk to
about this? Glen.

10:16.417 --> 10:19.086
This man keeps in shape. It's discipline.

10:19.295 --> 10:22.996
I exercise for a couple of weeks, that's it.
I admire you.

10:26.968 --> 10:28.380
Well, you know...

10:28.596 --> 10:31.265
Could you fit all your exercise equipment
into your new apartment?

10:31.474 --> 10:33.632
Frank!

10:35.645 --> 10:39.477
- What new apartment?
- Glen and Muriel are separa...

10:39.691 --> 10:41.931
That was a secret. I feel horrible.

10:42.151 --> 10:45.650
- I could cut out my tongue.
- Here's a knife.

10:45.863 --> 10:49.315
- No, really, I'm...
- You split up?

10:49.534 --> 10:51.574
No.

10:51.786 --> 10:54.110
- No!
- No!

10:54.330 --> 10:57.497
- Then why...?
- It's...

11:02.213 --> 11:08.086
You know I'm starting that new business?
Well, it takes a lot of time and energy,

11:08.302 --> 11:13.130
and when I'm with J... Muriel, I just...

11:13.350 --> 11:18.344
I am so crazy about her
that all I can think about is...

11:22.066 --> 11:25.400
- You know.
- Yeah.

11:25.612 --> 11:31.485
So I thought I'd move out for a while
and I'd be able to get some work done.

11:31.702 --> 11:33.990
[flatulence sounds]

11:35.038 --> 11:40.079
It's nobody's business what you two do.
You have no kids. You're both barren.

11:40.293 --> 11:45.833
Frank, I almost forgot to ask you.
How is Tina's hit-and-run case coming?

11:47.133 --> 11:49.209
- Hit-and-run case?
- Yeah.

11:49.427 --> 11:52.963
When Tina got drunk
and ploughed into that school bus?

11:53.182 --> 11:56.136
Ploughed? She just scraped paint off it.

11:56.351 --> 11:59.638
The brakes failed. Everyone was fine.
The kids, the nuns.

11:59.856 --> 12:05.229
I just thank God she wasn't in one of
those little sports cars like your girlfriend's.

12:05.444 --> 12:07.982
- They're death-traps.
- What?

12:08.197 --> 12:11.032
His girlfriend drives a Chrysler.
Big blue one.

12:11.242 --> 12:14.111
She's not my girlfriend!

12:16.830 --> 12:19.452
She's an instructor at the gym. I met...

12:19.666 --> 12:24.294
I left my gym bag at the gym
and she was bringing it back to me.

12:27.092 --> 12:31.966
I guess you have time to notice
these things now that you're not working.

12:32.180 --> 12:35.134
What happened?

12:35.349 --> 12:37.093
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

12:37.309 --> 12:40.145
There was a little cutback at Ed's place.

12:40.355 --> 12:43.272
They let go of some of the employees
that were...

12:43.482 --> 12:46.898
Selling company secrets.
Pass the butter, please.

12:47.112 --> 12:50.148
That's a lie and I'll prove it in court!

12:50.365 --> 12:53.282
- This Friday, right?
- We got a continuance.

12:53.493 --> 12:56.862
The court dockets were too filled
with drunk-driving cases.

12:57.079 --> 12:59.155
I skidded on a wet spot!

12:59.374 --> 13:02.541
- Somebody get her a drink.
- Get her a barrel.

13:02.752 --> 13:06.038
Please. Why must this happen
every time we get together?

13:06.256 --> 13:09.340
Can't this man have peace?
Hasn't he earned it?

13:09.550 --> 13:13.844
Delivering newspapers at four years old,
his little toes frozen.

13:14.055 --> 13:18.100
- It's all right.
- No. We've lost our sense of values.

13:18.309 --> 13:22.770
Maybe it's not mine to say, but
Nora and I... Come up here, sweetie...

13:22.981 --> 13:27.358
and Joseph and Jonas and little Josiah
on the way...we lead a simple life.

13:27.569 --> 13:30.570
We have each other,
and what the heck else is there?

13:30.781 --> 13:33.153
Joe-Joe, I'm just going to the market.

13:33.367 --> 13:34.397
Oh!

13:34.617 --> 13:37.286
Molly! Come here.

13:39.664 --> 13:44.493
These are my nieces and nephews.
Everyone, this is Molly.

13:44.712 --> 13:47.250
- Hi!
- Hi.

13:48.548 --> 13:52.083
- You wanted to see me?
- Would you buy some Oreos?

13:52.302 --> 13:56.347
We wouldn't be out of Oreos
if somebody hadn't eaten the insides

13:56.557 --> 13:59.594
and tossed the rest away,
you naughty boy.

13:59.810 --> 14:02.763
I'm old and rich.
I'll eat whatever parts I want.

14:02.979 --> 14:07.143
- If I want to eat the goddamn box, I will.
- Who wound you up today?

14:07.360 --> 14:10.563
- Better give me some money, then.
- Here.

14:12.448 --> 14:16.231
Take an extra hundred.
You might see something you want.

14:16.451 --> 14:19.655
You are such a dear.

14:19.872 --> 14:21.746
- I'll see you later.
- Bye.

14:21.957 --> 14:23.997
Toodles!

14:40.310 --> 14:43.263
These are good melons. Yeah.

14:45.773 --> 14:47.565
Sweet, juicy.

14:47.775 --> 14:49.186
- Uncle Joe?
- Mm?

14:49.402 --> 14:51.146
- Who...?
- Mm?

14:52.239 --> 14:56.983
- Who...?
- Oh, that's Molly. She's living here.

14:57.201 --> 15:00.618
Housekeeper? Secretary?

15:00.830 --> 15:04.745
Well, not exactly. She's sort of...my nurse.

15:04.960 --> 15:09.621
- Nurse?
- Yeah. I decided I wanted a nurse.

15:12.843 --> 15:16.046
Someone to ease my suffering.

15:16.262 --> 15:18.006
An agency sent her?

15:18.223 --> 15:21.508
No, she delivered a pizza one night
and we got to talking.

15:21.726 --> 15:27.765
Turns out she'd like to be a nurse, so...
Yeah, she helps out in various ways.

15:31.236 --> 15:34.071
She's become very special to me.

15:54.509 --> 15:56.337
[cheering]

15:56.679 --> 15:59.135
Yeah!

16:02.434 --> 16:04.474
[inaudible]

16:23.038 --> 16:26.657
Thank you, Fred.
Hello, everyone. I'm Chris Schenkel.

16:28.502 --> 16:31.254
Thank you. Thank you very much.

16:31.463 --> 16:33.503
On behalf of the Pro Bowlers Tour,

16:33.716 --> 16:37.299
we'd like to thank the people
of Milwaukee for their support.

16:37.512 --> 16:41.296
The top five qualifiers tomorrow
will begin play at 2.30.

16:41.516 --> 16:43.057
Shit.

16:44.143 --> 16:47.761
[female] You do this every time!
You ruin every vacation.

16:47.981 --> 16:51.764
- [male] Shut up!
- [female] It's always ''Let's drive a little further.''

16:51.985 --> 16:55.732
[female] Then there's no place to stay
and we wind up in a shithole!

16:55.947 --> 16:58.865
This is...this is unbelievable.

16:59.075 --> 17:01.114
Everywhere I stay, I'm next to this couple.

17:01.327 --> 17:02.738
[crockery smashes]

17:02.955 --> 17:05.624
Not literally them,
but people just like them.

17:05.833 --> 17:08.867
- It's like a franchise.
- [male] You made my life hell!

17:09.085 --> 17:12.251
- [female] Kiss my ass!
- [male] That would take all night!

17:12.464 --> 17:14.502
[door slams]

17:16.426 --> 17:18.549
Oh, God.

17:20.473 --> 17:22.511
You know, this is really stupid.

17:22.723 --> 17:26.590
ABC gives me a suite at the Marriott
and we're at the Bates Motel.

17:26.810 --> 17:28.140
Let's get out of here.

17:28.355 --> 17:31.855
Honey, you know
I get embarrassed at your hotel.

17:32.067 --> 17:36.776
Everyone always says, ''How's a schlep
like McTeague afford the Marriott?''

17:36.989 --> 17:40.322
''He sleeps with Robin Hunter,
the telecast producer.''

17:40.534 --> 17:44.579
''Really? He must screw better
than he bowls.''

17:44.788 --> 17:47.161
I do, don't I?

17:48.292 --> 17:51.992
I can't take it, Robin. I can't do it any more.

17:52.212 --> 17:54.370
What?

17:55.591 --> 17:58.509
- I'm giving up bowling.
- Why?

17:58.720 --> 18:04.306
My wrist. It's a pre-arthritic condition
and it's not going to get better.

18:04.516 --> 18:08.680
- You saw a doctor?
- No, Al the janitor at the bowling alley.

18:08.896 --> 18:11.897
He seemed to know his stuff
and took me right away.

18:12.108 --> 18:14.729
Of course I saw a doctor!

18:14.986 --> 18:19.030
I don't know. Cincinnati's
the last tournament of the season.

18:19.240 --> 18:22.573
I'm just going to bowl there and...that's it.

18:24.829 --> 18:26.905
Sweetheart.

18:33.671 --> 18:35.498
I'm sorry.

18:35.715 --> 18:40.424
I just wish for once
I could've finished in the top five,

18:41.513 --> 18:45.592
gotten on the national telecast just once.

18:45.808 --> 18:47.848
That would have been nice.

18:50.605 --> 18:53.891
- What are you going to do?
- Well...

18:54.109 --> 18:58.605
some guys offered to make me a partner
in this new bowling centre.

18:58.822 --> 19:03.069
They offered me 25% interest
for a 1 0% investment, 'cause I'd run it.

19:03.284 --> 19:04.743
It's a good deal.

19:04.953 --> 19:08.323
- It's great.
- Only I don't have the cash.

19:08.540 --> 19:11.078
- They want 300,000.
- Phew!

19:11.292 --> 19:14.958
So then I thought
maybe I'd be happy teaching.

19:15.172 --> 19:16.500
Yeah?

19:16.715 --> 19:23.085
Only, then you'd always
make more money than me.

19:23.305 --> 19:26.306
Who cares about that crap?
If you're happy teaching,

19:26.516 --> 19:31.013
then that makes me happy.
That's it. That's all there is.

19:34.316 --> 19:39.441
Her name is Molly Richardson.
She's 24 years old. She's English.

19:39.655 --> 19:43.605
She came here two years ago
as a nanny for a couple named Holcomb.

19:43.826 --> 19:48.821
When Mrs Holcomb eventually fired her,
Mr Holcomb attempted to kill himself.

19:49.040 --> 19:50.368
God.

19:50.582 --> 19:54.532
She bounced from job to job:
bikini model, physical therapist...

19:54.753 --> 19:57.873
- We're dead.
- ..until she started delivering pizzas.

19:58.090 --> 19:59.418
It pays to have skills.

19:59.634 --> 20:04.793
She moved in with Joe about three weeks
ago and she's been there ever since.

20:05.014 --> 20:06.473
As a nurse?

20:06.682 --> 20:09.885
She seems to spend
most of her time swimming.

20:10.978 --> 20:14.430
- In the nude. Here are some pictures.
- What?

20:15.650 --> 20:18.401
- Whoa.
- Oh, my God.

20:18.611 --> 20:22.194
- Are they having sex?
- Grow up. What do you think?

20:22.406 --> 20:24.649
She's going to get everything.

20:27.162 --> 20:31.111
That's the way these old guys are.
Biggest son of a bitch ever:

20:31.332 --> 20:35.200
she touches his old noodle
and his brains turn to frozen yoghurt.

20:35.420 --> 20:36.748
You would know.

20:36.963 --> 20:40.213
She'll screw him six feet under
and get everything.

20:40.426 --> 20:44.505
That's our money, and no English bitch
is gonna screw us out of it.

20:44.721 --> 20:47.426
Are they sleeping together?
Is there proof?

20:47.640 --> 20:51.970
- I need more time.
- They're humping too quick for pictures?

20:52.187 --> 20:55.521
- Let's get a better detective.
- How do we know you're any good?

20:55.733 --> 20:58.982
She found out you were fired
and that Glen left Muriel.

20:59.193 --> 21:03.026
My guy knew about Tina
while the car was still spinning.

21:03.239 --> 21:08.116
Yeah? Look at these pictures she got
of Glen and that gym instructor.

21:08.328 --> 21:10.866
Yeah.

21:12.915 --> 21:13.947
That's not me.

21:14.167 --> 21:17.288
It looks like you
and that's all that matters.

21:17.504 --> 21:22.001
- Use your gun!
- Glen, cut it out! Come here. Stop it.

21:22.217 --> 21:25.882
Stop it!
Don't you see what's happening here?

21:26.096 --> 21:28.054
Yeah, you're out of Scotch.

21:28.265 --> 21:31.017
Oh, Tina, go lie down.

21:31.227 --> 21:35.935
We caused this. All the backbiting
and the greed and the detectives.

21:36.149 --> 21:40.477
We've made each other look filthy.
Now it's come home to roost.

21:40.694 --> 21:43.316
Not one of us has the credibility

21:43.531 --> 21:47.031
to convince Uncle Joe that this girl
is just after his money.

21:47.243 --> 21:51.454
It's not our fault! It's his.
Sweet old Uncle Joe.

21:51.663 --> 21:55.079
We were all decent people
till he got his hooks into us.

21:55.293 --> 21:58.626
Except for Frank.
Frank was always a son of a bitch.

21:58.838 --> 22:03.630
It's true. Uncle Joe does this to us.
