and sliding down a banister?

01:07:28.645 --> 01:07:32.594
Honey, she's a vixen.
She's not giving him his medicine,

01:07:32.816 --> 01:07:36.979
she's gonna get his money
and dump him in a home. l know this.

01:07:37.195 --> 01:07:39.484
So it's not the money, it's your uncle.

01:07:39.697 --> 01:07:44.324
Exactly. He's opened up his heart to me,
you know.

01:07:44.535 --> 01:07:49.080
We've rekindled something
that we haven't had since l was a kid.

01:07:49.290 --> 01:07:53.039
l mean, we got a bond growing here.

01:07:53.253 --> 01:07:56.835
Danny, l love you and l believe in you.

01:07:58.509 --> 01:08:03.004
But isn't everything you're telling me
a big crock of bubbling shit?

01:08:03.221 --> 01:08:05.759
- No.
- lt's just the money.

01:08:05.974 --> 01:08:09.758
- lt's not.
- Mr Daniel.

01:08:09.978 --> 01:08:13.312
Your uncle has requested another chorus.

01:08:13.524 --> 01:08:17.520
- Come with me. Just leave.
- All my stuff's here.

01:08:17.736 --> 01:08:21.069
- All my clothes.
- l've seen your clothes. Just leave.

01:08:21.281 --> 01:08:24.198
Shall l tell him you're coming, sir?

01:08:27.330 --> 01:08:29.535
lt's not the money.

01:08:40.384 --> 01:08:43.917
[Danny as Durante]
He's back! Ha-cha-cha-cha-cha!

01:08:54.857 --> 01:08:59.151
- More wine, sir?
- No, thank you, Douglas.

01:08:59.361 --> 01:09:03.027
- ls the chicken Kiev satisfactory?
- lt's excellent.

01:09:03.240 --> 01:09:07.737
Could you tell the cook that tomorrow
l'd like to have broiled salmon again?

01:09:07.953 --> 01:09:12.532
- Very good, sir.
- ls my uncle going to swim today?

01:09:12.750 --> 01:09:16.250
He's not at home, sir.
He took the shuttle to Washington.

01:09:16.462 --> 01:09:20.330
- Business trip.
- Yes and no, sir.

01:09:20.550 --> 01:09:23.835
- What does that mean?
- He took Miss Molly along.

01:09:25.638 --> 01:09:26.966
He did?

01:09:27.182 --> 01:09:30.799
Yes. He had me book
the honeymoon suite at the Coolidge Hotel.

01:09:31.560 --> 01:09:33.600
Honeymoon?

01:09:35.189 --> 01:09:37.229
More wine, sir?

01:09:44.825 --> 01:09:49.617
This is a matter of life or death.
These are Mr McTeague's pills.

01:09:49.828 --> 01:09:55.785
l have to get them to him in two minutes
and 45 seconds. l need the room number!

01:09:56.002 --> 01:09:58.920
l'm sorry, sir.
Mr McTeague was very specific.

01:09:59.130 --> 01:10:02.335
No one is to have his room number.

01:10:02.551 --> 01:10:05.800
- l'll see to it that he gets the pills and...
- No!

01:10:07.347 --> 01:10:10.681
No! No, you don't understand.

01:10:10.893 --> 01:10:17.144
These pills only work if l give them to him
myself. lt's a very rare condition.

01:10:17.357 --> 01:10:21.818
Excuse me, sir.
Does this say ''moron''?

01:10:24.698 --> 01:10:28.613
l will leave him your message.
Would you like a room?

01:10:28.828 --> 01:10:30.570
l'm his nephew.

01:10:30.788 --> 01:10:34.536
- Oh, his nephew.
- Yes.

01:10:34.749 --> 01:10:41.038
Because he gave specific instructions
not to give his room number to relatives.

01:10:43.800 --> 01:10:48.843
What's the matter with you? Do you
not care about this hotel's reputation?

01:10:49.056 --> 01:10:52.841
There is an old man shacked up here
with a very young girl.

01:10:53.061 --> 01:10:58.434
Sir, most of these rooms have old men
with young girls. This is Washington.

01:10:59.942 --> 01:11:03.987
All right, listen, pal. Just give me...

01:11:06.991 --> 01:11:09.945
..a room. A cheap one.

01:11:10.160 --> 01:11:12.200
Of course.

01:11:23.967 --> 01:11:26.588
[Uncle Joe] Come on, Molly. Drink up.

01:11:40.859 --> 01:11:42.187
[knocking]

01:11:42.402 --> 01:11:44.858
Yeah, come in. lt's open.

01:11:46.740 --> 01:11:48.567
Right there.

01:11:49.660 --> 01:11:52.280
- Leaving?
- Yeah.

01:11:57.167 --> 01:12:00.251
- Where's Molly?
- She's taking a walk.

01:12:01.797 --> 01:12:04.168
We had a fight.

01:12:05.800 --> 01:12:08.422
Nothing serious, l hope.

01:12:08.636 --> 01:12:12.469
Be honest. Do you think Molly
would even like me if l wasn't rich?

01:12:12.682 --> 01:12:16.301
Look, l don't want to say
anything against her.

01:12:17.604 --> 01:12:19.763
But like you say, let's be honest.

01:12:20.232 --> 01:12:23.435
How many girls like that
are with poor old guys?

01:12:23.653 --> 01:12:26.607
- Take some towels.
- What?

01:12:26.822 --> 01:12:30.108
For what they charge,
you should take everything.

01:12:30.326 --> 01:12:34.620
l'm trying to figure out a way
to get the bed out of here.

01:12:34.830 --> 01:12:38.246
You are some piece of work,
do you know that?

01:12:40.086 --> 01:12:42.623
She's a good kid.

01:12:44.256 --> 01:12:47.423
That's why she can't...

01:12:47.635 --> 01:12:51.680
She can't...
can't just get herself to... You know.

01:12:53.725 --> 01:12:57.804
You mean you two didn't...?

01:12:59.188 --> 01:13:01.477
No.

01:13:01.690 --> 01:13:07.611
You know, l never believed
that anyone could love me for me.

01:13:09.574 --> 01:13:13.322
How could l,
when my own mother didn't?

01:13:15.037 --> 01:13:16.781
She didn't?

01:13:16.998 --> 01:13:19.952
She left me and my brother at a...

01:13:23.506 --> 01:13:26.956
..at a home in Albany when l was three.

01:13:27.175 --> 01:13:31.089
No note, no nothing.
Never asked about us.

01:13:31.304 --> 01:13:33.760
Never said, ''l'm sorry.''

01:13:38.853 --> 01:13:41.179
Your mother has to love you.

01:13:42.273 --> 01:13:43.471
Right?

01:13:43.691 --> 01:13:48.983
So even if no one else does,
she has to, doesn't she?

01:13:51.741 --> 01:13:55.193
Well, if my own mother
couldn't love me, l...

01:14:03.129 --> 01:14:05.001
I...

01:14:08.216 --> 01:14:10.838
l love you, Uncle Joe.

01:14:14.223 --> 01:14:16.050
You do?

01:14:17.476 --> 01:14:19.718
Yeah, l do.

01:14:23.441 --> 01:14:25.599
Take me home, Danny.

01:14:29.614 --> 01:14:32.483
[Robin] He's throwing her out of the house?

01:14:32.699 --> 01:14:35.736
Honey, just wait a second, will you?

01:14:39.123 --> 01:14:42.706
- Danny!
- Honey, l had no choice.

01:14:42.919 --> 01:14:46.916
She wasn't going to bring him back
till she got what she wanted.

01:14:47.131 --> 01:14:49.669
You mean until she got what you wanted.

01:14:49.884 --> 01:14:52.173
Honey, it's not like that.

01:14:53.263 --> 01:14:57.971
Look, Uncle Joe and l, we talked.
l mean, we really talked.

01:14:58.183 --> 01:15:01.683
He's been in Washington.
Some military contract.

01:15:01.896 --> 01:15:07.318
- Oh, yeah?
- We're going to go and see his attorneys.

01:15:07.527 --> 01:15:10.979
From now on, honey,
l'm going to be responsible for him.

01:15:11.197 --> 01:15:15.491
l'm gonna be here with him,
and...you know.

01:15:18.663 --> 01:15:20.703
Rich.

01:15:22.209 --> 01:15:25.992
- What about the deal with your cousins?
- My cousins are animals!

01:15:26.212 --> 01:15:29.130
They would put him in a home
if they could.

01:15:29.340 --> 01:15:31.583
l'll take care of their children,

01:15:31.802 --> 01:15:35.253
you know, give each kid
like a scholarship or something,

01:15:35.473 --> 01:15:37.927
but my cousins don't deserve anything.

01:15:38.141 --> 01:15:41.308
- You bastard!
- Frank, no!

01:15:41.519 --> 01:15:44.805
- Whatever happened to ''Hello''?
- We heard every word.

01:15:45.024 --> 01:15:47.479
- Did you listen at my door?
- Always.

01:15:47.693 --> 01:15:51.939
- l had no idea how sick you guys were.
- Come spend a day with us.

01:15:52.155 --> 01:15:55.073
- l'd rather shove this up my ass.
- l'll do it.

01:15:55.283 --> 01:16:01.572
- You're playing a lone hand, huh?
- l never agreed to anything with you.

01:16:02.499 --> 01:16:05.666
l only said l'd see
how things were with my uncle.

01:16:05.877 --> 01:16:08.499
l saw, and it made me sick.

01:16:08.714 --> 01:16:14.384
- You bastard.
- l like it better from her. lt's the accent.

01:16:14.595 --> 01:16:17.881
- l thought l'd find you together.
- We're not together.

01:16:18.098 --> 01:16:20.137
Right.

01:16:21.727 --> 01:16:25.226
Do you know, l thought
you were different than the others.

01:16:25.439 --> 01:16:27.765
But you're exactly the same.

01:16:27.984 --> 01:16:31.815
l am looking out for my uncle, OK?
For his welfare.

01:16:32.029 --> 01:16:35.113
Bullshit. They were willing
to wait until he died.

01:16:35.324 --> 01:16:37.482
But you're going to eat him raw.

01:16:37.701 --> 01:16:41.699
- Wait. Danny is not like that.
- Try to remember something, OK?

01:16:41.914 --> 01:16:44.370
ln the long run, nobody likes a tease.

01:16:44.584 --> 01:16:48.795
You are a cheap,
chiselling, low-life hustler.

01:16:49.005 --> 01:16:52.539
- [Carl] You said it!
- Well, it takes one to spot one.

01:16:58.431 --> 01:17:00.258
- Stop it!
- Great!

01:17:00.474 --> 01:17:04.555
Now you stop it,
after she gets in a shot.

01:17:05.730 --> 01:17:10.938
l'll give you half a million dollars to leave.
Cash. Soon as l get the money.

01:17:11.153 --> 01:17:14.069
Better than delivering pizza,
even in a good year.

01:17:14.280 --> 01:17:19.406
She gets that and we get a couple
of lousy scholarships? That's not fair!

01:17:19.619 --> 01:17:23.569
No, l will give you half a million dollars
and you leave.

01:17:23.790 --> 01:17:26.957
You'll give me half a million?
l'm getting it all!

01:17:27.168 --> 01:17:30.952
He sees right through you.
You're a walking fish-tank, baby.

01:17:31.173 --> 01:17:35.041
- You and your tan tushy can...
- l'll sleep with him.

01:17:36.386 --> 01:17:38.674
What?

01:17:38.888 --> 01:17:44.014
- What, you're...you're gonna...?
- As soon as he gets back from work.

01:17:44.227 --> 01:17:46.897
l'll give him a right good one.

01:17:48.107 --> 01:17:50.349
You... See, it wouldn't...

01:17:50.568 --> 01:17:54.435
He wouldn't be interested in that.
lt wouldn't even matter.

01:17:54.655 --> 01:17:58.439
lt'll matter. l'll make it matter.

01:18:07.042 --> 01:18:08.915
# Inka dinka doo #

01:18:11.338 --> 01:18:13.331
Molly.

01:18:13.549 --> 01:18:17.250
Do you know that both of my daughters
are named Molly?

01:18:17.470 --> 01:18:19.675
Oh, God.

01:18:19.888 --> 01:18:21.928
Oh, God.

01:18:26.103 --> 01:18:29.852
Oh, God. You think she'll do it?

01:18:31.109 --> 01:18:32.353
Yes, l do.

01:18:32.568 --> 01:18:36.483
You've given her no choice.
She'll do it just to beat you.

01:18:36.697 --> 01:18:40.648
Oh, Jesus. You think it'll work?

01:18:42.287 --> 01:18:44.743
A young girl with a body like that?

01:18:44.956 --> 01:18:49.333
There'll be nothing left of him
but a smile and an old hat.

01:19:03.099 --> 01:19:05.673
Welcome home, Joe.

01:19:10.399 --> 01:19:12.437
Hello, Molly.

01:19:16.654 --> 01:19:18.694
[inaudible]

01:19:19.449 --> 01:19:22.236
l'm tired. l'm going upstairs.

01:19:24.163 --> 01:19:25.158
Uncle Joe!

01:19:30.460 --> 01:19:31.456
Wait!

01:19:31.670 --> 01:19:34.375
Sir, will you need my assistance?

01:19:34.589 --> 01:19:37.959
No, Molly will assist me.

01:19:39.219 --> 01:19:41.841
Oh, l see. Very good, sir.

01:19:43.057 --> 01:19:45.345
Let's go.

01:19:49.939 --> 01:19:54.066
Sir? May l ask for a reference
before you go upstairs?

01:19:54.276 --> 01:19:56.352
Not now, Douglas.

01:20:00.449 --> 01:20:03.236
Goodbye, sir.

01:20:03.453 --> 01:20:06.406
Uncle Joe, wait! Please wait.

01:20:06.622 --> 01:20:10.999
- l have a surprise for you.
- Danny, don't.

01:20:13.838 --> 01:20:14.917
Up we go.

01:20:18.343 --> 01:20:21.012
His face! Did you see it?

01:20:21.220 --> 01:20:24.091
l've never been in one of these before.

01:20:25.100 --> 01:20:26.642
[Uncle Joe] Hang on!

01:20:33.608 --> 01:20:35.849
Molly, let me say something.

01:20:36.069 --> 01:20:39.852
No. Don't say anything.

01:20:41.450 --> 01:20:45.613
- A little young for you, ain't she, Joe?
- Who's there?

01:20:49.916 --> 01:20:52.074
Hi, Joe. lt's been a long time.

01:20:53.086 --> 01:20:57.214
- lt's Daniel.
- Daniel?

01:21:01.135 --> 01:21:07.257
- What are you...? You got so old.
- You're no Monet yourself.

01:21:10.020 --> 01:21:13.435
Molly, this is my cousin Daniel.
Danny's father.

01:21:15.066 --> 01:21:18.601
Danny asked me to come.
He's got a real regard for you.

01:21:18.820 --> 01:21:24.242
He made me think that maybe things
are different than the way l remember them.

01:21:24.451 --> 01:21:28.034
But they're not, are they?
lt's still the same.

01:21:28.246 --> 01:21:32.742
God, this place still stinks from greed.

01:21:32.959 --> 01:21:35.332
Those who have it...

01:21:36.505 --> 01:21:38.712
and those who want it.

01:21:46.181 --> 01:21:47.675
Dad!

01:21:48.976 --> 01:21:54.053
- Hello, Daniel.
- You came! That was great of you.

01:21:55.065 --> 01:21:57.390
- l'm leaving.
- What?

01:21:57.610 --> 01:22:00.611
God. They're all still here.

01:22:00.821 --> 01:22:05.698
First your parents, now you. He'll outlive
your children and leave them nothing.

01:22:05.911 --> 01:22:07.487
You wanna lighten up?

01:22:07.703 --> 01:22:12.032
You know who ruins this world?
The greedy. That's it.

01:22:13.417 --> 01:22:17.083
They have it. l want it.
l have it. l want more.

01:22:17.297 --> 01:22:20.630
That's the real pollution. Greed.

01:22:23.177 --> 01:22:25.585
You know who l think ruins the world?

01:22:25.805 --> 01:22:31.262
Pompous, self-righteous, holier-than-thou
middle-aged fanatics in pony-tails

01:22:31.477 --> 01:22:34.395
who give away their kids' toys!

01:22:36.774 --> 01:22:40.393
- He's got you too, huh?
- No, he doesn't have me.

01:22:40.612 --> 01:22:43.946
- Can't the truth be in between?
- No!

01:22:44.157 --> 01:22:46.944
One way is all right,
one way is all wrong.

01:22:47.159 --> 01:22:49.532
His way or my way. Pick.

01:22:49.746 --> 01:22:51.121
- Dad.
- Pick!

01:22:56.378 --> 01:22:58.704
- You are just so...
- Pick!

01:23:02.175 --> 01:23:04.962
All right, then l pick him.

01:23:07.514 --> 01:23:11.464
At least he doesn't take himself
so goddamn seriously.

01:23:42.508 --> 01:23:44.465
l'm leaving.

01:23:46.345 --> 01:23:48.338
Why?

01:23:49.474 --> 01:23:54.716
l can't believe l was almost
going to screw the old boy for money.

01:23:55.938 --> 01:23:59.521
l suppose maybe l've always
been here for the money.

01:23:59.733 --> 01:24:02.604
Christ, l make myself sick.

01:24:02.821 --> 01:24:05.145
l have to get out of here.

01:24:06.366 --> 01:24:07.942
l understand.

01:24:09.619 --> 01:24:12.738
You'll take care of him, won't you?

01:24:13.498 --> 01:24:15.241
Of course.

01:24:15.458 --> 01:24:19.326
You're not going to put him in a home?

01:24:19.546 --> 01:24:20.624
Never.

01:24:24.258 --> 01:24:26.168
Bye.

01:24:39.608 --> 01:24:42.146
Hey. You OK?

01:24:43.779 --> 01:24:44.942
Yeah.

01:24:46.157 --> 01:24:50.782
God, that was some scene
with your father. l just...

01:24:53.622 --> 01:24:55.032
What?

01:24:57.042 --> 01:24:58.786
That wasn't my father.

01:25:01.045 --> 01:25:03.583
What?

01:25:03.798 --> 01:25:08.377
That was an actor.
My father wouldn't come here on a bet.

01:25:11.015 --> 01:25:13.968
- So you just...?
- lt was my only shot, honey.

01:25:14.184 --> 01:25:17.802
He wanted me to pick him over my father.

01:25:18.021 --> 01:25:20.691
Yes, and you said you never would.

01:25:20.899 --> 01:25:24.732
l didn't. l picked him over an actor.

01:25:27.073 --> 01:25:29.479
- Don't touch me.
- What?

01:25:29.700 --> 01:25:32.784
- Hey. Come on. What's the matter?
- Danny.

01:25:32.995 --> 01:25:36.162
You dropped your compass in the woods
and you're lost.

01:25:36.373 --> 01:25:37.999
l'm not lost.

01:25:38.209 --> 01:25:42.586
- You don't see how sick this is?
- No!

01:25:42.796 --> 01:25:47.874
- Who got hurt?
- The truth got hurt. OK?

01:25:48.094 --> 01:25:52.092
lntegrity, self-respect,
decent human behaviour got hurt.

01:25:52.306 --> 01:25:56.434
l will be good to him.
Tell me who else will be as good.

01:25:56.643 --> 01:26:00.179
- That's not the point.
- No, that is the point.

01:26:01.399 --> 01:26:05.895
We've been through a lot together
and l think l've been pretty loyal.

01:26:06.112 --> 01:26:08.602
Honey, you've been great.

01:26:08.822 --> 01:26:13.818
But if you touch one cent
of your uncle's money, we're through.

01:26:15.413 --> 01:26:17.786
- What are you, crazy?
- l mean it.

01:26:17.999 --> 01:26:22.660
lf you take any of that money,
l will have no respect for you.

01:26:22.879 --> 01:26:26.461
Jesus! You sound like my father.

01:26:26.674 --> 01:26:31.384
No, l sound like the actor
who played your father. Enjoy your money.

01:26:38.019 --> 01:26:40.344
- Daniel McTeague Junior.
- Here.

01:26:44.777 --> 01:26:48.644
Your great-uncle has chosen,
for reasons l assume he's explained,

01:26:48.863 --> 01:26:51.021
to transfer to you all his assets,

01:26:51.241 --> 01:26:56.484
including full control of his commercial,
personal and financial affairs.

01:26:56.706 --> 01:26:59.576
My boy. My good boy.

01:27:00.709 --> 01:27:05.834
l would like to give you a full picture
of your great-uncle's holdings.

01:27:06.047 --> 01:27:10.378
The McTeague Scrap Metal Company,
comprising scrapyards, trucking...

01:27:10.594 --> 01:27:12.219
Excuse me.

01:27:14.223 --> 01:27:18.517
Uncle Joe, there's something
l'd like to explain to you.

01:27:20.479 --> 01:27:24.477
First of all, when l came
to your birthday party that time,

01:27:24.692 --> 01:27:30.030
l had no idea this was going to happen.
l wasn't after your money.

01:27:30.238 --> 01:27:34.189
l know that. That's why l love you.

01:27:39.790 --> 01:27:42.660
Joe. l have to tell you something.

01:27:42.876 --> 01:27:44.251
What?

01:27:46.172 --> 01:27:47.714
l'm...

01:27:49.258 --> 01:27:52.212
going to take such good care of you.

01:27:54.306 --> 01:27:56.594
You're a good boy.

01:27:57.850 --> 01:28:00.009
ls that it?

01:28:00.937 --> 01:28:03.475
- Yeah.
- Well, that was lovely.

01:28:04.190 --> 01:28:08.519
As l was saying, the McTeague
Scrap Metal Company, comprising...

01:28:08.735 --> 01:28:13.482
- Stop! Sign nothing!
- What the hell is this?

01:28:13.699 --> 01:28:16.736
Oh, my, my, my.

01:28:16.954 --> 01:28:19.409
lf deceit has a name, it's his name!

01:28:25.253 --> 01:28:30.794
Daniel, is it true? ls everything
these gerbils have been telling me true?

01:28:34.846 --> 01:28:36.885
Dad.

01:28:37.098 --> 01:28:38.094
Dad?

01:28:38.308 --> 01:28:41.891
Yes, Dad. Daniel McTeague Senior, his father.

01:28:42.104 --> 01:28:47.099
His real father, not the actor he hired
to come to your house last night.

01:28:48.194 --> 01:28:50.020
Danny.

01:28:52.989 --> 01:28:55.563
They told me that, Daniel.

01:28:58.329 --> 01:29:00.286
ls it true?

01:29:02.082 --> 01:29:04.538
Yeah. lt's true.

01:29:06.837 --> 01:29:13.374
You hired an actor to pretend he was me,
and then pretended to fight with him?

01:29:13.594 --> 01:29:17.342
And told him
you preferred Uncle Joe to me?

01:29:17.556 --> 01:29:21.340
Well, when you put it like that,
it sounds kind of bad.

01:29:21.560 --> 01:29:26.389
l know we've had our differences.
And l know you think l'm strange.

01:29:26.608 --> 01:29:28.564
No. No, Dad.

01:29:28.775 --> 01:29:32.608
l am. But l've always respected you,
Daniel. Always.

01:29:32.821 --> 01:29:35.739
l've always felt you had real character.

01:29:35.950 --> 01:29:37.195
Ha-ha!

01:29:40.121 --> 01:29:42.825
- Does money mean this much to you?
- No.

01:29:43.040 --> 01:29:46.124
l didn't go and see Uncle Joe
for the money.

01:29:46.335 --> 01:29:51.875
We made a deal. lf he kept the money
in the family, he'd get a cut. Right?

01:29:52.091 --> 01:29:54.629
- Yes, but...
- Then he double-crossed us.

01:29:54.845 --> 01:29:57.928
Because they're scum! They're greedy!

01:29:58.139 --> 01:30:01.639
We're greedy? We were willing to share.

01:30:02.810 --> 01:30:04.389
Dad.

01:30:05.480 --> 01:30:10.900
l don't know what happened.
l just got...sucked in.

01:30:11.110 --> 01:30:15.322
First one thing didn't seem wrong,
then another, until...

01:30:15.532 --> 01:30:17.940
Nothing seemed wrong.

01:30:18.160 --> 01:30:21.077
l know. That's why l left.

01:30:35.302 --> 01:30:39.346
- How are you, Joe?
- l'm still eating grapes.

01:31:02.871 --> 01:31:05.956
- Uncle Joe.
- Save it.

01:31:07.418 --> 01:31:12.792
OK, Joe. Bare knuckles, toe to toe.
We've spent 20 years eating your shit

01:31:13.007 --> 01:31:17.086
and saying, ''Mm! What a cook.''
No more. We've hired attorneys.

01:31:17.302 --> 01:31:20.968
lf we don't get our share,
we'll get you declared incompetent.

01:31:21.182 --> 01:31:23.803
And we'll win,
because we found out things.

01:31:24.018 --> 01:31:27.102
You've got toys in the attic. Broken toys.

01:31:27.814 --> 01:31:31.977
And we'll hammer on you
until you cave in. Understand?

01:31:32.192 --> 01:31:35.442
- Or is your mind already gone?
- All right!

01:31:38.700 --> 01:31:41.369
Sit down. All of you.

01:31:42.495 --> 01:31:44.321
- Uncle Joe...
- Quiet.

01:31:55.092 --> 01:31:57.083
Go ahead.

01:31:57.302 --> 01:32:00.468
As l was saying
before the circus came to town,

01:32:00.680 --> 01:32:02.839
your uncle's holdings at their peak

01:32:03.058 --> 01:32:08.349
held a net - net, mind you -
financial value of just under $25 million.

01:32:12.275 --> 01:32:16.225
At the moment, however,
he is $95,000 in debt.

01:32:25.621 --> 01:32:30.201
- Wait a minute. He's...?
- ln debt beyond the value of his assets.

01:32:35.257 --> 01:32:38.127
The room, is it doing this?

01:32:40.095 --> 01:32:43.345
l fear this has come as a shock to you.

01:32:43.557 --> 01:32:48.897
No. Shitting a sailboat, that's a shock.
This is a fucking catastrophe!

01:32:49.813 --> 01:32:53.313
The trip to Washington
was not for a military contract.

01:32:53.525 --> 01:32:58.353
lt was to work out an arrangement
with the lRS to keep Joe out of jail.

01:32:58.573 --> 01:33:02.866
That has been accomplished,
but everything is lost.

01:33:03.076 --> 01:33:07.240
Plus some arrangement
must be made for the 95,000.

01:33:11.585 --> 01:33:15.037
How the hell do you lose $25 million?

01:33:16.132 --> 01:33:17.756
lt's easier than you think.

01:33:17.967 --> 01:33:22.675
l overextended, made loans,
some claims the government wouldn't allow.

01:33:22.889 --> 01:33:26.554
- The penalties were...
- Hold it. l don't believe this.

01:33:26.767 --> 01:33:29.602
lt's another one of his tricks.
A little test!

01:33:29.812 --> 01:33:32.434
l will put you in touch with the lRS.

01:33:32.648 --> 01:33:37.145
They'll give you a full accounting
and a brochure for the auction.

01:33:37.361 --> 01:33:41.573
- Auction?
- They're taking my home.

01:33:41.783 --> 01:33:44.737
Damn it! Stupid, stupid!

01:33:44.952 --> 01:33:49.200
We played along!
We should've stepped in five years ago!

01:33:49.415 --> 01:33:51.492
Two would have been enough.

01:33:51.710 --> 01:33:54.545
You stupid, pathetic old man.

01:33:54.755 --> 01:33:57.375
Goddamn it! One more word out of you,

01:33:57.590 --> 01:34:01.919
l'll kick your ass so high up
you'll take off your shirt to shit!

01:34:02.136 --> 01:34:04.046
Come on.

01:34:04.264 --> 01:34:06.637
Come on, bowling boy!

01:34:09.977 --> 01:34:12.184
Stop it!

01:34:12.397 --> 01:34:14.436
Frank, cut it out!

01:34:20.072 --> 01:34:24.401
- Stop! l've got a metal plate in my head.
- You do?

01:34:24.617 --> 01:34:26.409
No!

01:34:28.037 --> 01:34:32.036
- That's enough.
- Get security to the conference room.

01:34:32.251 --> 01:34:35.252
That's enough. Get over here.

01:34:36.422 --> 01:34:38.330
Meathead!

01:34:38.548 --> 01:34:41.086
You're insane, you know that?

01:34:41.301 --> 01:34:45.299
Me? For five years, l begged you,
let's put him in a home!

01:34:45.514 --> 01:34:50.756
No, you didn't want to. You didn't have
the balls! None of you have any balls!

01:34:52.270 --> 01:34:53.551
Frank?

01:34:53.772 --> 01:34:56.524
l've been waiting to do this a long time.

01:35:03.532 --> 01:35:04.943
Stop it.

01:35:05.159 --> 01:35:06.819
Come on.

01:35:07.036 --> 01:35:10.322
- l want them out of here!
- lt's all right!

01:35:15.461 --> 01:35:17.453
We were...

01:35:17.671 --> 01:35:20.293
We were just leaving, anyway.

01:35:21.175 --> 01:35:23.796
- What do we do now?
- Nothing!

01:35:24.012 --> 01:35:27.381
We wait around and dance at his funeral.

01:35:50.997 --> 01:35:53.120
You're still here.

01:35:55.085 --> 01:35:58.916
How long have you known you were broke?

01:35:59.130 --> 01:36:01.668
About a year.

01:36:01.883 --> 01:36:03.508
A year.

01:36:03.719 --> 01:36:10.255
So this whole time you were...what?
Schmucking with me? Every second.

01:36:10.475 --> 01:36:13.642
Danny, please, l had to find out,

01:36:13.853 --> 01:36:17.554
to know who'd care for me
when they knew l had nothing.

01:36:17.774 --> 01:36:22.935
And care will be required.
Your uncle's condition is degenerative,

01:36:23.155 --> 01:36:27.152
and whoever assumes control
over his finances

01:36:27.367 --> 01:36:29.823
must oversee the liquidation of his assets,

01:36:30.037 --> 01:36:32.742
be responsible
for the outstanding balance,

01:36:32.956 --> 01:36:35.412
and, of course, there's our bill.

01:36:35.626 --> 01:36:38.412
We will need you to sign these papers.

01:36:38.628 --> 01:36:41.036
lf you'd just told me the truth.

01:36:43.592 --> 01:36:47.507
l mean, l'm not saying
l'm a perfect guy or anything,

01:36:47.722 --> 01:36:53.344
but then maybe l could have felt
some compassion, some responsibility.

01:36:53.560 --> 01:36:55.802
Just the truth!

01:36:57.481 --> 01:37:01.693
The truth is, l'm an old guy.
l'm broke. l need help.

01:37:01.903 --> 01:37:04.654
Not now! Then.

01:37:05.739 --> 01:37:07.981
Now's no good.

01:37:08.200 --> 01:37:10.952
Now's too late.

01:37:11.161 --> 01:37:14.366
l crawled. l begged.

01:37:16.334 --> 01:37:18.907
l lost my girlfriend.

01:37:20.462 --> 01:37:22.918
l hate that you did this.

01:37:24.342 --> 01:37:28.210
Danny, l had to.
l had to find out who loved me.

01:37:28.430 --> 01:37:32.379
- Who...
- Nobody. Nobody loved you.

01:37:34.268 --> 01:37:35.597
Why should they?

01:37:38.064 --> 01:37:43.937
What's there to love?
What about you is there to love?

01:38:03.715 --> 01:38:08.592
l want a camera on the kid's father
when the kid's shooting the free throws.

01:38:08.804 --> 01:38:12.932
lf he misses, the expression
on the dad's face is another Emmy.

01:38:13.141 --> 01:38:15.180
Find the dad.

01:38:18.022 --> 01:38:21.106
- Mike, go back.
- Hey!

01:38:22.693 --> 01:38:25.230
- Stop!
- Girlie, if you don't sit down...

01:38:25.445 --> 01:38:28.019
Will you shut up a second?

01:38:32.203 --> 01:38:34.326
[man] l'll meet you over there.

01:38:46.718 --> 01:38:49.255
What happened?

01:38:49.471 --> 01:38:51.758
Uncle Joe was broke.

01:38:51.972 --> 01:38:54.545
- Come on.
- Broke.

01:38:54.767 --> 01:38:59.145
No, not just broke. ln debt.

01:38:59.355 --> 01:39:04.232
Everybody pushing and shoving,
and all the time the trough was empty.

01:39:08.531 --> 01:39:12.066
When did l get so obsessed with money?

01:39:12.284 --> 01:39:14.610
When did that happen?

01:39:15.705 --> 01:39:19.240
l mean, you've known me for years.
l was never like that.

01:39:19.459 --> 01:39:21.285
Was l?

01:39:21.502 --> 01:39:23.377
No.

01:39:27.634 --> 01:39:31.797
- What's going to happen to him?
- Uncle Joe?

01:39:32.013 --> 01:39:35.097
l assume my cousins will hang him.

01:39:35.308 --> 01:39:37.182
No, really.

01:39:38.895 --> 01:39:40.852
Really.

01:39:42.107 --> 01:39:45.357
l don't know. l don't care.

01:39:46.570 --> 01:39:47.850
You don't?

01:39:48.071 --> 01:39:51.522
Allow me to face up to it.
l wasn't there for him.

01:39:51.741 --> 01:39:54.114
l was there for the money, boom.

01:39:55.537 --> 01:40:00.246
That time when he told you
how scared he was to go into a home?

01:40:00.458 --> 01:40:03.662
You told me you felt sorry for him.

01:40:03.878 --> 01:40:05.836
l did.

01:40:06.506 --> 01:40:10.551
But don't you see? lt was an act.
He was putting on an act.

01:40:10.761 --> 01:40:14.425
- Anybody would have felt sorry for him.
- Even your cousins?

01:40:20.771 --> 01:40:23.772
[workman] Make sure you get
plenty of padding on there!

01:40:25.150 --> 01:40:27.309
Put it in last.

01:40:31.741 --> 01:40:33.983
Douglas. Douglas.

01:40:34.869 --> 01:40:36.363
Where's Uncle Joe?

01:40:36.579 --> 01:40:41.573
l couldn't say, sir.
l'm no longer in your uncle's employ.

01:40:41.792 --> 01:40:44.828
- What?
- He can no longer pay my wages.

01:40:46.046 --> 01:40:49.084
Wages?
Don't you care what happens to him?

01:40:50.259 --> 01:40:53.628
Very droll, sir. Most amusing, sir.

01:40:53.887 --> 01:40:58.217
- Watch your back. Coming through.
- Where is he, in a nursing home?

01:40:58.434 --> 01:41:00.972
Out of the question. He can't afford it.

01:41:01.188 --> 01:41:05.481
Hey. What...? What's he going to do?

01:41:05.691 --> 01:41:10.649
He can go dance the hully-gully
for all l care. Good day, sir.

01:41:37.057 --> 01:41:40.889
[doctor being paged over tannoy]

01:41:47.692 --> 01:41:49.815
Where's your hat?

01:41:51.279 --> 01:41:54.364
Went in the auction. A buck's a buck.

01:41:54.575 --> 01:42:00.031
Your lawyer told me you were here.
What are you doing in the hospital?

01:42:00.247 --> 01:42:02.655
l didn't feel good, stupid.

01:42:02.874 --> 01:42:06.540
- But a county ward?
- lt's all l can afford.

01:42:07.629 --> 01:42:13.133
lronic, huh?
l'm right back where my mother left me.

01:42:13.343 --> 01:42:18.254
